==Early==
* '''?''' - [[Mabel Suffield|Mabel Tolkien]] moves her family, from [[King's Heath]] to a house in [[Edgbaston]] next door to the [[Birmingham Oratory]] and the [[Grammar School of St. Philip]]. To save money, Mabel removes the boys from [[King Edward's School]] and enrolls them in St. Philips.

* '''[[13 April|13]]''' - [[Godfrey Kenton]], the voice of [[Aragorn]] and [[Mablung (ranger of Ithilien)|Mablung]] in the [[The Lord of the Rings (1955 radio series)|1955 radio series of ''The Lord of the Rings]]'', is born.
==June==
* '''[[11 June|11]]''' - Illustrator [[Eric Fraser]] is born.
==September==
* '''[[26 September|26]]''' - [[Clyde S. Kilby]], literature professor, is born.
